overcome shyness at school i am sort of shy at school in front of my peers i'm more of the quiet type and i don't feel very comfortable when my peers are talking to me it's like i don't know what to talk about and i'm scared that i will bore them and they won't think i am fun it seems like everyone has a good sense of humour and can make each other laugh i can't seem to do that it's just that i don't know what to talk about do you guys have any advice for me i'm an extremely shy person around people i don't know as well if you don't have a life pretend to have one do some research on the internet magazines books etc so you can talk about hobbies you'd like to take up but don't flat out lie if people find out that you aren't a world famous model for rock climbing they are not going to like you Social rule Shyness Theory of conduct The Catcher in the Rye Shaggy dog story Time Out of Mind Avenue Q Richard Feynman The nature of God in Western theology Germaine Greer The Amber Spyglass The Ashlee Simpson Show Humphrey Bogart Jon Secada Kodocha Internet troll Love-shyness The Silence (The Twilight Zone) Friends Carl Barks Canadian literature Alignment (role-playing games) Sharon Tate Undergrads Autism Singlish The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Buddy Guy Infantilism Squidward Tentacles The Third Eye (radio programme) Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Nico Robin Homeschooling Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Anchor Anderson Cooper Reservoir Dogs Recumbent bicycle Philosophical skepticism Masturbation Extreme Programming True Crime: Streets of LA Galaxy Angel Peer review Harem anime Street photography 3rd Rock from the Sun Another Side of Bob Dylan Transactional analysis Woody Allen A Course In Miracles Advanced Squad Leader The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Aesthetic Realism Okashina Okashi Humour Hikikomori Autism rights movement Family Guy The Emancipation of Mimi Survivor (novel) Counter-Strike Eric Cartman Communication skill Milton H. Erickson Aerial 